window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p><b>“A Doc Ford novel has more slick moves than a snake in the mangroves. In </b><b><i>Captiva</i></b><b>, Randy Wayne White takes us places that no other Florida mystery writer could hope to find.”—Carl Hiaasen</b></p> <p>Randy Wayne White is acclaimed as \"wildly inventive\" (<i>The San Diego Union-Tribune</i>), \"a wonderful writer\" (Paul Theroux), \"a fine storyteller\" (Peter Matthiessen), and \"the rightful heir to John D. MacDonald\" (<i>The Tampa Tribune-Times</i>). Now he delivers a wicked thriller that sends government agent-turned-marine biologist Doc Ford into dangerous new waters, as a Florida fishing dispute escalates into a deadly war that reaches across the ocean...</p>"; 
